languages.text: "Всегда удивляло, что преподобный Иеронимус использует крошечную часовню в Атриуме для проповедей. На Футфоле есть куда более подходящие его статусу храмы".
"I am forever astonished that Reverend Hieronymus makes do with that shoebox of a chapel in the Atrium for his sermons. Footfall has several temples far more befitting his status."

languages.text: “每次看到希罗尼穆斯牧师，我都很惊讶。落脚港明明有好几座神殿，更加符合他的尊贵身份，可他总是在中庭那座比鞋盒大不了多少的小教堂里进行布道。”
languages.original_text: "I am forever astonished that Reverend Hieronymus makes do with that shoebox of a chapel in the Atrium for his sermons. Footfall has several temples far more befitting his status."

languages.text: «Me sorprende enormemente que el reverendo Hieronymus se limite a usar esa diminuta capilla del Atrio para sus sermones. Hay varios templos en Paso mucho más acordes con su estatus».

languages.text: 「ヒエロニムス師が説教のために アトリウムの礼拝堂を利用していることにはいつも驚かされる 。フットフォールには彼の地位にふさわしい神殿がいくつもあるだろうに」
languages.original_text: "I am forever astonished that Reverend Hieronymus makes do with that shoebox of a chapel in the Atrium for his sermons. Footfall has several temples far more befitting his status."

languages.text: "Ich bin immer noch erstaunt, dass sich Reverend Hieronymus mit diesem Schuhkarton von Kapelle im Atrium für seine Predigten zufrieden gibt. Auf Footfall gibt es einige Tempel, die seinem Status angemessener wären."
languages.original_text: "I am forever astonished that Reverend Hieronymus makes do with that shoebox of a chapel in the Atrium for his sermons. Footfall has several temples far more befitting his status."

languages.text: « Dire que le révérend Hiéronymus prononce ses sermons dans cette cage à lapins de l'Atrium qui lui sert de chapelle. Plusieurs autres temples sur Castel conviendraient bien mieux à un homme de sa stature. »
